WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.210
(v) - Subtitles and captions are necessary

00:02.210 --> 00:04.990
(v) to help keep the internet accessible for everyone.

00:04.990 --> 00:06.530
(v) Let me tell you a little more about

00:06.530 --> 00:08.370
(v) how to use them on Vimeo.

00:11.470 --> 00:13.010
(v) Subtitles provide viewers

00:13.010 --> 00:15.200
(v) with the video's dialogue in written form,

00:15.200 --> 00:17.270
(v) while captions include subtitles,

00:17.270 --> 00:18.590
(v) but also a written description

00:18.590 --> 00:20.613
(v) of what's occurring in their videos.

00:21.500 --> 00:23.850
(v) If a video has subtitles or captions,

00:23.850 --> 00:26.940
(v) you'll see a CC button in the play bar of a video.

00:26.940 --> 00:29.220
(v) Simply click on it and then choose the caption

00:29.220 --> 00:31.920
(v) or subtitle track you'd like to see.

00:31.920 --> 00:34.960
(v) Video creators upload captions and subtitles themselves,

00:34.960 --> 00:36.620
(v) so if you don't see your language,

00:36.620 --> 00:38.250
(v) it means the video has not yet been

00:38.250 --> 00:39.940
(v) transcribed or translated.

00:39.940 --> 00:42.060
(v) In that case, you can contact the creator

00:42.060 --> 00:44.550
(v) to see if they're able to add them for you.

00:44.550 --> 00:47.730
(v) If you want to add captions or subtitles to your own video,

00:47.730 --> 00:49.580
(v) go to your video settings page,

00:49.580 --> 00:52.920
(v) choose the distribution tab and then go to subtitles.

00:52.920 --> 00:55.350
(v) Click the plus symbol to add a new file,

00:55.350 --> 00:58.510
(v) select the language and whether it's captions or subtitles,

00:58.510 --> 01:00.440
(v) and click choose file.

01:00.440 --> 01:02.970
(v) If you need help creating a subtitle or caption file,

01:02.970 --> 01:04.500
(v) read further into this help article

01:04.500 --> 01:06.250
(v) for some great resources.

01:06.250 --> 01:08.460
(v) We support a variety of different file formats

01:08.460 --> 01:09.790
(v) in all of these languages,

01:09.790 --> 01:12.280
(v) which this help article dives into as well.

01:12.280 --> 01:13.770
(v) Thanks for helping make the Internet

01:13.770 --> 01:15.093
(v) more accessible for all.

